// Rule ids whose dedicated InvalidFiles fixture the validator does not reject
// as an error under the all-flags-on config. Each remaining entry is one of:
//
//   - Best-practice recommendation (SHOULD): the check runs but emits at
//     warning severity, so the fixture is not an error-match. The conformance
//     suite asserts these against the SBOL2_bp corpus as warnings. This covers
//     the ontology rules (10511, 10528, 10529, 10706, 10707, 11905, 12007,
//     13505) and the sequence/component/combinatorial best-practice rules
//     (10518, 10520, 10523, 10711, 10712, 10903, 11907, 12909, 12910, 12911,
//     12912, 12913, 13006, 13018, 13019, 13020, 13021, 13022).
//
//   - Cross-document / resolver-dependent: detecting the violation needs
//     objects outside this document. 10808, 10811 (a MapsTo remote resolved in
//     another document), and the cross-document CombinatorialDerivation rules
//     12908, 13005, 13011, 13012, 13016, 13017. The in-document portions of
//     10526 and 11609 are checked strictly; only their cross-document remote
//     resolution stays deferred.
//
//   - Reader-scope: 12301, 12303 require the reader to synthesize a
//     GenericTopLevel from an unknown SBOL-namespace top-level type; 10106
//     requires the reader to retain the declared XML namespace bindings, which
//     the RDF graph discards after parsing. These are reader changes outside
//     the validator's scope.
//
//   - 10302 compares wasDerivedFrom version ordering, outside the local
//     structural subset implemented here.
//
//   - 13403 has no dedicated catalog rule (absent from the 268-rule set).
//
// Kept explicit so the strict/loose match set is auditable and grows over time.
[
    "sbol2-10106",
    "sbol2-10302",
    "sbol2-10511",
    "sbol2-10518",
    "sbol2-10520",
    "sbol2-10523",
    "sbol2-10528",
    "sbol2-10529",
    "sbol2-10706",
    "sbol2-10707",
    "sbol2-10711",
    "sbol2-10712",
    "sbol2-10808",
    "sbol2-10811",
    "sbol2-10903",
    "sbol2-11905",
    "sbol2-11907",
    "sbol2-12007",
    "sbol2-12301",
    "sbol2-12303",
    "sbol2-12908",
